Police in Marsabit Central have launched investigations into the death of area OCPD Abel Sande.The probe began after Sande's body was discovered in his house on Christmas Day.They said preliminary findings indicated that the officer possibly died of a heart attack."Sande had failed to pick his calls. When the station commander went to check his house, he found him dead in his bed," police said. The body was moved to a mortuary in Meru county in wait for a postmortem.Sade had served at Marsabit Central for just one month, having been transfered from Bomet following complaints of biasness.